            <creation>This story, with the short title "Pious Deacon Eats with a Blacksmith," is recent: the earliest PEMM manuscript* in which this story appears is from around <date>1850</date>.Originally composed in <placeName ref="LOC3010Ethiop">Ethiopia</placeName></creation>
            <abstract>
                <p>A deacon in the town of Babba faithfully served Mary in the church. Satan envied this deacon and inspired the people of Babba to complain that he ate and drank with a blacksmith. When the local ruler confronted the deacon with this charge, the deacon insisted that Mary’s love was his only food and drink. But his accusers went before the ruler once more, as as they again bore false witness, an angel of the Lord appeared and struck them down. The local ruler prostrated before the deacon as the townspeople marveled at this sign.</p>
            </abstract>
